<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pawn1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pawn,</orth> subst. 1) something given as a security, a pledge: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 3, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.91" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.853" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 853</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.74" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.55.74" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.55.74" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 55</bibl> <cit><quote>to lay to p.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 5</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.113" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 113</bibl>. <cit><quote>to leave in p.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.839" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 839</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) a stake hazarded in a wager: <cit><quote>my life I held but as a p. to wage against thine enemies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 157</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) the state of being pledged: <cit><quote>redeem from broking p. the blemished crown,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.293" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 293</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my honour is at p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 3, 7</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>